1.The __init__.py code has a critical issue that causes the routes in register_api.py to potentially not be registered correctly, which is also one of the main reasons for the 404 error. The detailed analysis is as follows:
Problem: The CORS configuration does not include the registration of the API, and the import method may not trigger the route registration
The CORS configuration only allows the login interface, and the registration interface will be restricted by cross-domain requests

CORS(app, resources={r"/api/login": {"origins": "*"}})

This means that only the /api/login interface allows cross-domain requests, while the /api/register interface is not included.

2.The register.js code only completed the "front-end form validation" (checking for non-empty username, password length, and consistency of the two passwords).
It lacks the core logic of "sending the data to the backend registration interface".
New addition: Sending a request to the backend registration interface (core supplementary part):
fetch('http://127.0.0.1:5000/api/register', 
     { 
      method: 'POST', // 
      headers: {
        'Content-Type': 'application/json', // 
      },
      body: JSON.stringify({ // 
        username: username,
        password: password
      })
    })
The interface address must be correct: the address in fetch, http://127.0.0.1:5000/api/register, must be exactly the same as the backend interface (the port and path cannot be wrong).
The backend service must be started: run python -m backend.app.main to ensure that the backend is running on port 5000. Otherwise, an "network error" will be reported.
The login page path must be correct: window.location.href = 'login.html' where login.html should be in the same folder as register.html (if not, the path needs to be adjusted, such as ../login.html).
The field names in the form must match: registerForm.username and registerForm.password in the code, should be the same as the name attribute of the input boxes in your register.html (for example, the input boxes should have name="username"):

